variables of mean zero valued in some inner product space, then the `L^p`-norm of `X‚āĀ + ... + X‚āź` is
at most `C‚āö` times the `L^(p/2)`-norm of `|X‚āĀ|¬≤ + ... + |X‚āź|¬≤`, where `C‚āö` is a constant depending
on `p` alone.

